name: Bone Fighter
description: This Bone Fighter has been re-reanimated to serve once more.

name: Plague Zombie
description: Though fairly weak individually, the Plague-Spawned Zombies can become a huge threat enmasse.

name: Old Crone
description: Foolish foes might dismiss the Crones of Lys for their apparent infirmity. But as old as they look, some are in truth as old as the elder vampires, their lives unnaturally extended through their mastery of soul magic.

name: Clamp Trap
description: When an enemy Champion steps on this trap, it takes 8 Physical Damage and becomes pinned (cannot move) for 3 turns

name: Poison Trap
description: When an enemy Champion moves on or adjacent to this trap

name: Test Pack
description: Test Pack

name: Battle Lord
description: Sir Galahad stands first among brothers in the order known as the Knights of the Round. Though his brothers may call him Sir, the men he commands in combat know him only by his much-deserved title: Galahad, Battle Lord of Avalon.

name: Bone Giant
description: The bones of a Giant fetch a high price in the markets of the Necropolis, due largely to the reluctance of most Giant clans to part with the bones of either their living or their dead. Even so, from time to time a corpse becomes available to the Necromancers of Lys, and these terrible creations are often the result.

name: Bone Trap
description: A clever bit of Necromancy from the laboratories of Lys, this trap unleashes a previously-cast summoning spell when the mechanism is tripped. The spell will summon a Bone Fighter with 15 hitpoints to the closest unoccupied space.

name: Catapult
description: While these wheeled catapults lack mobility, their range and firepower give them a role in any army.

name: Court Wizard
description: The disciples of Merlin spend decades studying under the Archmage before they are trusted to practice magic alone. Many of these wizards take up postings within the noble houses of the realm, where they are counted upon to advise and protect their Lord in all matters civil and martial.

name: Dwarven Sergeant
description: Although most dwarves choose to fight in heavy plate, some few prefer mobility, allowing them to swiftly move to where the battle is thickest. These brave dwarves inspire those around them and tend to move into leadership roles quickly, provided they survive long enough.

name: Fire Elemental
description: Fire elementals are driven by rage and a hunger for mana. They will serve any master so long as the price is paid.

name: Knight of Avalon
description: The life of a Knight of Avalon is one of piety, brotherhood, and of constant martial training. These men live and die for their God, for their brothers, and for Avalon, in that order.

name: Peasant Levy
description: The peasantry of Avalon are diligent and loyal stewards of the land. In times of great need, they are willing to answer their lord's call to fight.

name: Risen Archer
description: Many men enter a battlefield with a bow in their hands and leave with a hole in their heart. Such corpses are useful to the Necromancers of Lys, who can draw upon the spiritial memories of an archer's skills to power their undead creations.

name: Risen Mage
description: Undead Mages, unlike many Risen beings, are not necessarily slaves to their fate. Many mortal mages who lack the knowledge and power to achieve true immortality will freely offer themselves to the Necromancers of Lys. The closer in time the reanimation is to the death of the Mage, the more of the Mage's former self and knowledge are retained in the Risen creation.

name: Risen Warrior
description: The battlefields of the world are strewn with the corpses of men who, in life, could carry a shield and swing a sword. Necromantically speaking, it is an uncomplicated task to reanimate these corpses and direct them towards an opposing army.

name: Soul Catcher
description: The Soul Catcher is an advanced work of Necromantic artificing. When a living creature dies in the vicinity of the Soul Catcher, the device generates 10 mana for its owner.

name: Stone Warden
description: All dwarves share a magical connection with what they call the World Heart, and this connection is felt most strongly through stone. Stone Wardens dedicate their lives to cultivating and nourishing this connection, which can allow for awesome displays of magic in times of need.

name: Vampire Noble
description: The Vampiric Nobility of Lys keep an extremely tight reign on their dark gift, although they will not begrudge mages who seek immortality from achieving it on their own terms. Even so, there remains a cultural divide between self-made Immortals and those who are Immortal by birth, although both classes share in the rulership of the Necropolis.

name: Boneblade Staff
description: The equipped Champion has +2 Damage and Risen Commander

name: Meteor
description: Call a Meteor down from the sky, dealing 12 fire damage to all units in a radius of 1.

name: Peasant Archer
description: Many lords train their peasants in the use of the longbow. While these archers lack the accuracy and strength of professional bowmen, a massed volley can nevertheless be quite effective.

name: Man-at-Arms
description: These men are professional soldiers in the King's standing army. They are well-trained and well-equipped.

name: Veteran Sellsword
description: To these veteran fighters, titles and honors mean far less than a purse full of gold.

name: Sherwood Archer
description: The archers of Sherwood are widely famed for their bowmanship and woodcraft.

name: Sherwood Friar
description: There exists in the Sherwood a peculiar monastic order dedicated to the twin causes of brewing strong drink and to swindling coin from the nobility. This particular friar has such mastery over the first tenet of his order that he often forgets to pursue the second.

name: Village Healer
description: The position of Village Healer is one of authority and respect throughout Albion. Healers rely on their great knowledge of herbcraft as well as minor charms to tend to their flock.

name: Angelic Protector
description: The World-Father sends many blessings to the faithful of Albion. His Angels appear in times of great need to protect and preserve.

name: Forest Nymph
description: Nymphs are playful and somewhat mischievous creatures that can be found in many different environs. Those that dwell in the forests of Albion are prone to petty larceny, which they find completely hilarious.

name: Lady of the Lake
description: The Lady of the Lake has a peculiar interest in the affairs of men, and is known to bestow magical blades upon those whom she finds true of heart.

name: Holy Blade
description: The Holy Blade grants the wielder a powerful magical attack and +10 hitpoints.

name: Wise Owl
description: Many creatures of the forest carry ancient knowledge, especially amongst the owls, who see all that moves in the night.

name: Morgana la Fey
description: The Sorceress Morgana Le Fey has been feuding with the citizens of Camelot for decades. The so-called Once and Future King may be suffered to have his cities, but his arrogance in claiming all of Albion is a threat that cannot be ignored.

name: Fairy Drake
description: Fairy Drakes are shy but affable creatures. Their draconic heritage imbues them with an impressive strength of body and spirit, given their size.

name: Fairy Spellthief
description: Some fairies are made extremely jealous by observing others do magic that they cannot. Those with the power to act on their envy are known as spellthieves, whose tricks of magic can often lead to unexpected outcomes for all parties involved.

name: Lotus Fairy
description: Many fae creatures are magical hybrids with plants or animals. The Lotus Fairy is a particularly dangerous breed, especially to those unaware that it most decidedly does not observe a vegetarian diet.

name: World-Father Blessing
description: The World-Father blesses all units in a radius of 1, healing them for 5 and giving +1 DMG and +1 DEF for 5 turns.

name: Feydark Blessing
description: The spirits of the Fey bless all units in a radius of 1, granting them +1 SPD and Mobility for 5 turns.

name: Angelic Blessing
description: Target unit is cleansed of negative conditions and gains Flying.

name: Summon Battlespire
description: Create a 4-height castle tower on the targeted space. If the space is occupied then the occupant will be placed atop the tower if possible. This spell cannot be cast in a space adjacent to a Runestone or Nexus.

name: Mists of Avalon
description: Summon a shrouding fog to tiles in a radius of 1 for 5 turns, providing 50% protection to ranged attacks for all units standing within the fog.

name: Withering Curse
description: Cast a withering curse on the target unit, reducing its Damage by 5 and its Speed by 2 for 6 turns.

name: Holy Shield
description: Equipped unit gains +2 DEF and Divine Favor (When this unit would be healed, it is healed for 5 additional hitpoints).

name: Recalcify
description: Risen Units in an area with radius of 1 lose Brittle Bones and permanently gain +2 DEF

name: Cursed Life
description: Secret: The next opposing champion deployed to the battlefield gains the Cursed Life condition, losing 2 hitpoints per turn indefinitely.

name: Martyr
description: Target friendly champion with class Priest, Paladin, or Knight. For two turns, whenever a friendly unit would receive damage, the damage is reduced by 2 and then this unit receives it instead.

name: Banner of Avalon
description: Friendly Champions from the Camelot faction gain +5 Max HP and +1 DMG while this unit is in play

name: Banner of Lys
description: Friendly Champions from the Necropolis faction gain +5 Max HP and +1 DMG while this unit is in play

name: World-Father Cross
description: Champions from the Camelot faction standing adjacent to this structure can spend all of their action points to Pray, generating 1 Mana per action point spent in this way for its owner. Priests and Paladins that pray in this manner generate 2 additional mana.

name: Territorial Spriggan
description: Spriggans are forest spirits that create bodies for themselves out of natural materials. The 'male' spirits are extremely territorial and can be recklessly protective of their kith and kin.

name: Spriggan Tender
description: Spriggans are forest spirits that create bodies for themselves out of natural materials. The 'female' spirits enjoy nurturing and protecting the natural magic of the forest.

name: Ironbark Giant
description: The Ents of the Feydark forest are some of the oldest living creatures in the world. They are strong and well-protected by their thick bark, and are essentially unstoppable when drawn into combat in defense of their forest.

name: Risen Angel
description: A very few angels have forsaken the world-father to gain powers even He cannot offer. These foul creatures are fearsome traffickers in death and grow ever stronger in its presence.

name: Ritual Blade
description: When this unit kills an enemy champion with a basic attack, it is healed for 10 hitpoints and gains 1 stack of Empowered (+2 DMG)

name: Summon Brambles
description: Magical Brambles sprout in a radius of 1 from the targeted hex, dealing 8 physical damage to all units. The brambles last for 6 turns and cost an additional AP to traverse.

name: Feudal Knight
description: Feudal Knights are landed bannermen who can afford good armor and a warhorse. They are loyal to their lords and protective of their smallfolk, but tend to shy away from the more dramatic deeds aspired to by the Knights of Camelot.

name: Royal Wyvern
description: The King's ancestral affinity with dragonkind has led to Royal breeding programs for all manner of dragons. The Fire Wyvern is among the first and most successful breeds.

name: Forest Wyvern
description: The wild Wyverns of the Feydark use poison to weaken their foes before impaling them on their barbed tails.

name: City Blacksmith
description: The men dedicate their lives to shaping steel are as crucial to Albion's security as those who wear and wield it.

name: Marcus Sanguinius
description: Marcus is acknowledged as an elder among elders by the nobility of Lys. His mastery of blood magic is only surpassed by his unflinching cruelty towards the lesser races.

name: Plaguelord
description: Plaguelords are golems formed from the corpses of plague victims and animated by malevolent spirits. They are vile abominations deployed ahead of Lysian armies to terrorize their foes - and to recruit.

name: Tree Spider
description: These spiders hunt for birds high in the treetops. They are not web-spinners, instead using their webs to bind their foes from afar.

name: Aos Si Frostknight
description: The Aos Si court tends to shy from meddling in the affairs of this plane.That they have dispatched Frostknights to aid the Fey court

name: Oaken Wand
description: The equipped Champion gains Polymorph: Giant Toad. The Polymorphed unit is removed from play and redeployed as a giant toad with 30 max HP and the Polymorphed condition. If it loses the Polymorphed condition then it will be redeployed in its original form.

name: Giant Toad
description: While not exactly bred for battle, giant toads are excellent jumpers and are quite at home in the water.

name: Warding Cloak
description: The equipped Champion becomes Spell Sealed, and cannot gain or lose positive and negative conditions.

name: Druid Stones
description: A place of worship and reverence for the Fey folk. At the beginning its owner's turn, the Druid Stone grants 5 mana and 1 card draw if you control a champion with Race: Fey

name: Ancient Memories
description: Target Champion gains Race: Fey and Fey Commander.

name: Will o' Wisp
description: Wisps are relatively benign spirits content to drift through the forests without any particular aim.

name: Toki
description: Toki are golems fashioned by the fey folk to serve and protect. They are quite good at knocking things around.

name: Prince of Thieves
description: While the man is more famed for his skills at archery and his derring-do than his actual thieving, The Prince of Thieves has nevertheless proved a thorn in the side of civilized society for many years.

name: Gawain the Kind
description: Sir Gawain is widely known as a formidable and compassionate warrior. His sigil is the sun, leading some to speculate that he draws his magical strength from sunlight, but in fact his true strength is derived from his faith, his honor, and his love for all living things.

name: Brutish Thrall
description: Undeath is not a requirement to live in the Necropolis; only monstrosity.

name: Royal Plagueknight
description: Ever-increasing threats from the undead and other magical antagonists led the king to form a chapter of knights who are solely devoted to combating the unholy elements of the world

name: Brotherhood Assassin
description: Even a city of light has dark alleys for darker dealings. While their services might be distasteful to men of honor, honor tends to run in short supply outside of the knightly circles.

name: Duergar Shadowknight
description: The Necropolis has expanded deep into the underworld, where the ancient and hidden things reside. The Duergar, with their hatred of light and life, have made natural allies for Lysian explorers.

name: Envoy of Imhotep
description: Lys is not the world's only Necropolis. Far to the south, in a desert of scorching sands, lay the ruins of a once-great empire. The twisted sorcerors who rule there have sent their envoys far and wide in search of new allies - and new sources of magic.

name: Unholy Ballista
description: For those with the right knowledge and a bit of magic, bones can be coaxed into any number of creative uses.

name: The Green Knight
description: The Green Knight is known to be a formiddable warrior with powerful magical protections. He often engages in violent duels with Arthur's knights purely for entertainment.

name: Gargoyle
description: Contrary to outside expectations, the Necropolis is filled with houses of worship. These gothic cathedrals, devoted to their dark gods, are often protected by vigilant stone watchers.

name: Vampire Bat
description: Vampires share many traits with bats, and it is not uncommon for vampires to develop a bat-like appearance. Some few, with proper magical coaxing, are completely transformed into these terrible beasts.

name: Festering Ghoul
description: Ghouls are abominable creatures that feed on the carrion scraps that work their way into the underdepths of the necropolis. Should living things ever dare to venture below then the Ghouls are widely known to be a leading cause of disappearances.

name: Necromancer
description: The sorcerors who devote their lives to animating the dead are utterly bereft of conventional morality, driven by greed and a lust for everlasting life.

name: Centaur Reaver
description: Centaurs can be extremely territorial and are known to exact horrifying revenges upon those who violate their homelands.

name: Vampire Hunter
description: Driven by revenge, she travels the world hunting the hunters who stole those she loved most.

name: Sherwood Frostwitch
description: Arthur's Court can prove unwelcoming to young women who wish to learn the elemental magics on account of the long-standing feud with Morgana La Fey. As a result, various sects of 'witches' have taken up residence in the forest so that they can practice their art freely.

name: Ice Crystal
description: A magical elemental structure. Champions that begin their turns adjacent to this unit take 2 Frost damage; any unit that receives this damage becomes Slowed for 2 turns (-2 SPD). When this unit dies, it explodes into icey shards, dealing 8 frost damage to every adjacent unit.

name: Old Crone
description: Foolish foes might dismiss the Crones of Lys for their apparent infirmity. But as old as they look, some are in truth as old as the elder vampires, their lives unnaturally extended through their mastery of soul magic.

name: Grave Lurker
description: Found in the graveyards and sepulchers of the world, these impish creatures tear into their targets with needle-like claws.

name: Flame Skull
description: A necromantic construct capable of setting foes ablaze.

name: Barghest
description: While these beasts are perfectly natural in every regard, they have no instinctual aversion to the horrors of the Necropolis. As a result, many keep them as pets and guards.

name: Dwarven Linebreaker
description: Centuries of fighting on the underroads has led to Dwarves becoming experts at breaking through chokepoints. These Dwarves can rush into battle and knock enemies senseless while waiting for more agile infantry to fill in the gaps.

name: Dwarven Paladin
description: The teachings of the World-Father are not unknown to the Dwarves, although all good Dwarves know that the World-Father was a Dwarf and not a man. He is worshipped along with several other important gods in the Dwarven Pantheon.

name: Dwarven Cardinal
description: The Cardinals were Paladins who set their hammers aside as an act of penance and sacrifice. Their faith has been rewarded with more powerful magics.

name: Dwarven Miner
description: These Dwarves live to dig. To them, no greater joy exists than to find a rich vein of ore.

name: Dwarven Mason
description: The masons hold a revered position in Dwarven society. Their skill at shaping stone is unsurpassed throughout the entire world.

name: Stoneheart Statue
description: This statue protects Dwarves from all harm. When adjacent Dwarves would take damage from any source, they take 2 less damage.

name: Dwarven Sniper
description: The artificers of Undermountain have taken a keen interest in black powder and its various uses. Some warriors have sworn off their blades forever, believing that guns are the future of Dwarven Warfare.

name: Dwarven Axe Zerker
description: Dwarves who fight without wearing armor are widely considered to be mentally unstable. Even so, fighting unencumbered makes these Dwarves extremely dangerous over short distances.

name: Dwarven Bombcopter
description: Suicidal. Insane. Heretical. Dwarves of a more old-fashioned bent hate to see these contraptions take to the skies. Even so, their complaints tend to subside once they see the bombs start falling.

name: Chained Titan
description: They found it deep beneath their mountain, chained in a hidden cavern and filled with rage. They becalmed it with runes of control inscribed on its collar and set it free. Now it serves and protects all of Dwarfkind.

name: Blade Automaton
description: Dwarves have extremely long lives and reproduce very slowly. As a result, every single Dwarven death is considered a great tragedy. Even the stodgiest of Dwarves would agree that it is better by far to spend Warmachines than lives in battles where numbers will matter more than strength.

name: World-Father Priestess
description: She is royalty, and as such, could have had a life of ease and excess. Instead she chose penance and faith, and she now uses her magical skills to support her father's knights.

name: Dwarven Brewmaiden
description: The Dwarven War effort is fueled as much by ale as it is by courage. These specialist brewers provide both in good measure, and they've got a few tricks up their sleeves to boot.

name: Kaladim Flameheart
description: Kaladim is a living legend among the Dwarves. His most widely-known feat was to slay a red dragon on his one-hundreth birthday and to drink the heart's blood, which is generally a death-sentence. Instead Kaladim grew even stronger and has taken on some characterists of the fallen beast.

name: Web Widow
description: The Web Widow is not satisfied with birds or bats; she weaves her web in search of bigger game. There are few killers more cold and heartless than she in the Feydark.

name: Malevolent Queen
description: The realms of the Fey are vast and in it there are many courts. One such court is ruled by a vain and petty witch who, despite her shortcomings, commands powerful magics. Previous encounters with the Dwarven folk have filled her with a particular disdain for their kind.

name: Dwarven Runemaster
description: Dwarven Runemagic is a closely-kept secret. Those who are entrusted with the knowledge responsible for forging the most powerful Dwarven artifacts.

name: Dwarven Root Druid
description: Outsiders tend to overlook the importance of agriculture in Dwarven society, but one need only look up when standing in their massive halls to see what it is they farm: roots. Some Dwarves spend their entire lives climbing around in them, and over generations they have developed some Earth magic to assist their efforts.

name: World-Heart Locket
description: Centuries ago, the Dwarves thought to delve all the way to the World-Heart. They discovered many wonders, such as the ore from which this locket is crafted. Its bearer gains Stone Sense which grants defense and damage when occupying stone.

name: Grumpy Dwarf
description: Dwarves are widely known to hold grudges. The longer a grudge goes un-answered, the more pissed off a Dwarf can get. This Dwarf is in a particularly foul mood.

name: Centaur Ranger
description: Rangers roam far and wide, patrolling Centuar territory and keeping a sharp eye for good game.  These Rangers are swift and strong.

name: Forgotten Queen
description: She was a Queen once, long ago and far away. After devouring every last one of her subjects in a century-long orgy of blood and lust, she turned to the Necropolis in hopes of someday ruling again.

name: Dwarven Cannon
description: The Dwarven artificers have been hard at work on this prototype black powder cannon. It is a cumbersome piece of equipment but the firepower is unrivaled.

name: Dwarven Forge
description: The Dwarves are widely  known for their skill at forging weapons and armor. A lesser-known fact is that they are industrious recyclers as well.

name: Ariachne
description: The underworld expanse runs as surely below the Feydark as it does every other part of the world. The Demon Ariachne has made these subterranean caverns her home on account of the Feydark's abundance of natural spider allies. Her interests and those of the Fey courts are rarely in conflict, content as they are in their own realms, so a tolerable detente exists between the factions.

name: Steam Golem
description: Golem creation is a relatively well-known art among magical practitioners; however, the ongoing mana costs of maintaining these creatures typically limits them to defensive roles. Dwarven artificers have developed this Steam Golem in an effort to mitigate those drawbacks by integrating steamwork auxiliary power sources.

name: Reflection  Shield
description: Target unit gains a secret Reflection Shield, which reflects basic attacks made at a range greater than 1 back upon their attacker. The effect is revealed when it is first triggered.

name: Sky Hammer
description: Summon a magical hammer to strike your opponent. Target takes 10 physical damage, loses all AP, and becomes stunned for 2 turns.

name: Rockslide
description: Summon a rockslide to the targeted area, layering 2 tiles of stone in a radius of 1. Units caught in the rockslide take 8 physical damage and are knocked back 1 space. Cannot affect tiles adjacent to runestones or a Nexus.

name: Reverse Engineer
description: Shuffle a copy of every equipment in the targered area into your draw deck.

name: Flame Rune
description: Inscribe a Flame Rune on the target hex. Any unit standing on the Rune deals 5 extra fire damage when making a basic attack (extra damage ignores DEF). A hex may contain only one rune at a time.

name: Protection Rune
description: Inscribe a Rune of Protection on the target hex. Any unit standing on the Rune will take 5 fewer damage from all damage sources. A hex may contain only one rune at a time.

name: Control Rune
description: Inscribe a Rune of Control on the target hex. When a champion occupying this hex is destroyed, its card is shuffled into the draw deck of the player who cast this rune. A hex may contain only one rune at a time.

name: Healing Rune
description: Inscribe a Rune of Healing on the target hex. A champion occupying this hex at the start of its turn heals for 5 hitpoints. A hex may contain only one rune at a time.

name: Sealing Rune
description: Inscribe a Rune of Healing on the target hex and all adjacent hexes. A champion occupying this hex is Spell-Sealed and cannot gain or lose positive and negative conditions. A hex may contain only one rune at a time.

name: Boulder Trap
description: Place a secret boulder trap on the targeted space. When an enemy unit moves on or adjacent to that hex, the trap is triggered. Enemies adjacent to the trap take 5 physical damage and are knocked back one space and stunned.

name: World-Heart Flask
description: A flask made from gold mined in a very, very deep shaft. The equipped champion gains Purity and Regrowth.

name: Runed Shackle
description: The runes on this shackle bind its wearer to the earth. The equipped champion loses Flying and Hover, if it has them, and suffers from -2 SPD.

name: Embrittle Armor
description: All Champions in the targeted area (AOE 1) gain four stacks of the Sundered condition

name: Gore-Covered Axe
description: The equipped Champion gains Counterattack (when this Champion is attacked at range 1, it makes a free basic attack dealing its DMG to the attacker)

name: Mana Mine
description: The owner of this mine gains 4 mana at the start of their turn, plus 1 additional mana per friendly Dwarven Miner in play.

name: Orcish Reaver
description: Reavers are front-line Orcs who possess incredible strength and speed. Few men could stand toe-to-toe with one and live to tell the tall.

name: Hill Giant
description: Giants are notoriously dumb and slow. They live in small clans and are mostly nomadic hunters of giant beasts. It is not uncommon to see them employed by Orcs.

name: Hedge Knight
description: Hedge Knights are masterless wanderers that live a life somewhere between a professional soldier and a mercenary. They fight for pay and sometimes for honor, and they generally know their trade well-enough to afford their armor, if not a horse.

name: Orcish Enforcer
description: Orcs and Goblins naturally vacillate between the extremes of violence and sloth. Enforcers are drawn from the toughest and meanest of the Orcish hordes to compel obedience in the ranks.

name: Orc Peon
description: Peons are young Orcs with more brawn than brains. Most will never live beyond their first real battle and those who fall are not mourned.

name: Orc Shaman
description: Orcs are not ignorant of magic, although they generally fear it. The Blood and Poison magics worked by Orcish Shamans are both brutal and potent.

name: Goblin Knife Fighter
description: To survive among orcs, goblins need to be cunning or they need to be quick. Fast hands holding savage blades will make even an orc think twice about picking a fight.

name: Hill Goblin
description: The Chosen Steppe is a difficult country marked by enormous rock formations. Many Goblins choose to live in the upper reaches of these crags where their natural agility can be used to the greatest effect.

name: Warchief Mokillz
description: The Warchief earned his name with a promise: follow me, and I'll give you more kills. He killed those that refused to follow and kept his promise to those that did.

name: Goblin Slinger
description: One might be surprised how many times the fate of an entire battle has turned upon a single hero getting hit in the eye by a small rock.

name: Da Chef
description: While Orc armies can do very well living off the land - and the corpses of their opponents - they still have a surprsing amount of respect for those among them who dedicate their lives to the culinary arts.

name: Harpy
description: In the upper reaches of the Chosen Steppe, Harpies hunt n flocks for small game like Goblins. They can be convinced to take on scouting roles so long as they are well-fed for their efforts.

name: Cave Troll
description: The general perception of trolls as dumb and angry creatures is largely accurate. Trolls cannot be commanded so much as coaxed into battle.

name: Goblin Trapper
description: Goblin artificers are skilled at making all manner of devious traps, and it is not at all uncomonn for an Orc army to be preceded by Goblin trappers tasked with sowing some chaos behind enemy lines.

name: Quality Chainmail
description: Equipped Champion gains +2 DEF

name: Open the Armories
description: Friendly Peasants in the targeted area permanently gain the skill Minor Armor Piercing.

name: Field Fortification
description: A stout fortification that can hold a position and help direct archers.

name: Blessed Font
description: Adjacent friendly Champions are cleansed of negative conditions and healed for 5 hitpoints at the start of each turn.

name: Elemental Aegis
description: Target friendly unit gains Elemental Aegis.

name: Signal Flags
description: Equipped Champion gains Battle Coordinator

name: Jeweled Necklace
description: The equipped Champion gains Absorb fire and Explosive Death

name: The Lady's Favor
description: The equipped Champion gains Emboldened

name: Bestow Knighthood
description: Target only a human peasant. If that peasant has destroyed an enemy champion during this game, then remove it from play and spawn a Hedge Knight with the same hitpoints at its current location.

name: Avalon Faction Token
description: Whosoever possesses this token shall gain a full play set of Avalon Faction cards in Longsword Tabletop Tactics.

name: Stoneheim Faction Token
description: Whosoever possesses this token shall gain a full play set of Stoneheim Faction cards in Longsword Tabletop Tactics

name: Feydark Faction Token
description: Whosoever possesses this token shall gain a full play set of Feydark Faction cards in Longsword Tabletop Tactics

name: Necropolis Faction Token
description: Whosoever possesses this token shall gain a full play set of Necropolis Faction cards in Longsword Tabletop Tactics

name: Chosen Faction Token
description: Whosoever possesses this token shall gain a full play set of Chosen Faction cards in Longsword Tabletop Tactics

name: Helguard Faction Token
description: Whosoever possesses this token shall gain a full play set of Helguard Faction cards in Longsword Tabletop Tactics
